2026-04-16 12:20:33 | INFO     | DiagnosticAssistantLLM | OUTPUT: suggestion_type='hypothesis' action_type=None action_target=None action_description=None suspected_components=['Battery (inside power supply module)', 'Battery connections / holder in power supply module'] hypothesis_explanation='Direct measurement across the battery terminals and across the LED‑resistor branch in the power supply module shows 0 V everywhere, even with a battery inserted. This means the 12 V source is not being produced at all. Since the LED branch is wired directly across the source, a failure only in that branch would still leave 12 V measurable at the battery terminals. Therefore, the fault must be in the battery itself (discharged or internally open) or in its immediate connections/holder so that the battery is not actually connected into the circuit. Replacing or repairing the battery/holder should restore supply voltage and allow the rest of the chain (control modules and lamp) to operate normally.'
