2026-04-16 12:21:25 | DEBUG    | DiagnosticAssistantLLM | INPUT [tail only with new content. Full content is concatenation of all previous log entries]: 
Someone executed a (additional) diagnostic action on the system. The action (type, target_component, description, outcome) was: 
TYPE: Test,
TARGET: Series cabling between power supply module, control module chain, and load module,
DESCRIPTION: With the battery installed and PSU output confirmed good, sequentially probe voltage along the series path to locate where 12 V disappears. First, disconnect the PSU from the rest of the modules and identify which external cable is +12 V and which is 0 V by measurement. Then reconnect modules and, with all switches ON, measure voltage between the two cables at: (1) the input pair of Control Module 1, (2) the output pair of Control Module 1, then similarly at inputs/outputs of each subsequent control module up to the load module. At each point, determine whether you still have ~12 V across the pair or if polarity has flipped or voltage has dropped to 0 V, which would indicate a misconnection (cable swap) or open circuit at the last good point.,
RESULT: 12 V is present at PSU Output Cable (+) and propagates correctly through Control Modules 1 and 2, with corresponding low voltage on their (−) cables. The first point where ~12 V on the (+) line drops to near 0 V is at Control Output Cable (+) 3, and from that point onward (including the load) both (+) and (−) lines sit at ~0.0064 V, indicating the last confirmed good point is Control Input Cable (+) 3 / Control Input Cable (−) 3. No POLARITY INVERSION DETECTED in the measured cabling.
Current persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:
No circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.


2026-04-16 12:21:25 | INFO     | DiagnosticAssistantLLM | OUTPUT: suggestion_type='action' action_type='Test' action_target='Control Module 3 internal switch path and indicator LED branch' action_description='Open the inspection panel of Control Module 3. With the system powered and all switches set to ON, measure voltage at the module’s input pair (already known good), then at the switch terminals and at the module’s output pair inside the box to see whether 12 V is being interrupted by an open switch/contact or by an internal wiring fault. Also measure voltage across the indicator LED-resistor branch and check its continuity to determine whether the module’s internal circuit is open or shorted, causing the downstream line to collapse to ~0 V.' suspected_components=None hypothesis_explanation=None
2026-04-16 12:21:25 | DEBUG    | ServiceAgentSpiceSim | _parse prompt:
Available actions:
- observe_component: Visually inspect a component.
- measure_voltage: Measure voltage at component ports (w.r.t. ground) with a multimeter.
- measure_current: Measure the branch current through a component with a multimeter (ammeter mode).
- open_switch: Open a switch (set it to the off/open position). Safe to call even if already open.
- close_switch: Close a switch (set it to the on/closed position). Safe to call even if already closed.
- test_continuity: Measure resistance / continuity with a multimeter (ohmmeter mode).
- test_diode: Test a diode or LED forward voltage with a multimeter (diode-test mode).
- test_path_continuity: Measure the Thevenin resistance between a terminal of one component and a terminal of another (point-to-point continuity test).  params: {'source_port': 'str — port name on source component to probe (optional)', 'sink_port': 'str — port name on sink component to probe (optional)'}
- inspect_connections: Inspect which cables are physically connected to each port.
- invert_enclosure: Lift and invert an enclosure to look inside.
- restore_enclosure: Return an inverted enclosure to its normal orientation.
- rotate_enclosure: Rotate or move an enclosure to reposition it (e.g. break a line-of-sight coupling).
- open_peephole: Open a peephole to observe internal components.
- close_peephole: Close an open peephole.
- open_inspection_panel: Remove the inspection panel to access internal components for measurement.
- close_inspection_panel: Replace the inspection panel.
- replace_component: Replace a component with a new unit.  params: {'replacement_part_id': 'str — identifier of the replacement part', 'replacement_cost': 'float (default 1.0)'}
- adjust_potentiometer: Adjust the wiper position of a potentiometer.  params: {'new_position': 'float in [0.0, 1.0]'}
- verify_repair: Identify the component that the technician suspects is faulty and mark it for hypothesis verification (repair-and-test).
- move_led: Move a LED from its current module to another module LED slot. If the target slot already has a LED the two are swapped; if the target slot is empty the LED and its series resistor are moved.  params: {'target_module_id': "str — component_id of the target PhysicalEnclosure (e.g. 'cube_psu' or 'cube_ctrl3')"}
- short_ports: Bridge two component ports with a 0.01 Ω connection (models probing / wiring two circuit nodes together).  params: {'source_port': 'str — port name on source component to bridge (optional)', 'target_port': 'str — port name on sink component to bridge (optional)'}
- detach_sequence_of_control_modules_and_attach_it_to_power_and_load: Detach a contiguous sequence of control modules (source = first module, sink = last module) from the circuit and connect them directly between PSU and load to test if the load lights up.

System components:
Aggregates (Modules):
- module_psu: Power Supply Module (Components that are part of the module: battery, psu_green_led, psu_green_resistor, psu_cable_pos, psu_cable_neg, battery_internal_resistor)
- module_ctrl1: Control Module 1 (Components that are part of the module: ctrl1_switch, ctrl1_green_led, ctrl1_green_resistor, ctrl1_cable_in_pos, ctrl1_cable_in_neg, ctrl1_cable_out_pos, ctrl1_cable_out_neg)
