Instruction: Open the inspection panel of Control Module 3. With the system powered and all switches set to ON, measure voltage at the module’s input pair (already known good), then at the switch terminals and at the module’s output pair inside the box to see whether 12 V is being interrupted by an open switch/contact or by an internal wiring fault. Also measure voltage across the indicator LED-resistor branch and check its continuity to determine whether the module’s internal circuit is open or shorted, causing the downstream line to collapse to ~0 V.
